---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout hideNavbar={true}>

  <section class="min-h-screen px-6 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

      <h1 
        class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6 text-shadow-purple text-center"
        data-aos="fade-right"
      >
        Building My Portfolio
      </h1>

      <p 
        class="text-lg text-gray-400 mb-12 text-center"
        data-aos="fade-right"
        data-aos-delay="100"
      >
        Not a tutorial. Just me figuring things out and pretending I knew what I was doing.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-gray-300 text-lg leading-relaxed">

        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">The Idea</h2>
          <p>I didn't want another "here are my projects, please hire me" page. I wanted something that actually looks good — clean, smooth, and fun to scroll through. Basically I wanted this to look very cool.</p>
        </div>

        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="300">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Tech I Used</h2>
          <p>Went with <span class="text-primary font-bold">Astro</span> because it's fast and just makes sense. <span class="text-primary font-bold">Tailwind</span> handled the styling so I didn't spend three hours arguing with CSS over why something isn't centered.</p>
        </div>

        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="400">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Design</h2>
          <p><span class="text-primary font-bold">Dark theme</span> was obvious coz I'm not a freak. Luckily found a solid template online, loved the animated stars, then went a little too happy with the <span class="text-primary font-bold">murasaki</span> (yes that was a gojo reference). No regrets. Spent way too long tweaking spacing and hover effects but honestly that's just called having taste (I'm tired as hell).</p>
        </div>

        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="500">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">What I Learned</h2>
          <p>Technically not much. But turns out the small stuff hits different. Spacing, timing, tiny animations coz they're the difference between "this is a website" and "okay this actually feels nice." Worth the rabbit hole.</p>
        </div>

        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="600">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Is It Done?</h2>
          <p>Absolutely not. I'll keep tweaking, breaking, and fixing things indefinitely, or atleast until college completely consumes my soul. Whichever comes first.</p>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>